This paper presents a framework for learning fair and censored representations using generative adversarial networks. The paper involves techniques from machine learning, artificial intelligence, and computer vision, which are all covered by the arXiv categories cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CV. The paper also discusses privacy and security concerns, which are covered by the arXiv category cs.CR. Finally, the paper involves optimization and game theory, which are covered by the arXiv category cs.SI.
